WEBVTT

00:02.565 --> 00:05.071
In New York City's war on crime,

00:05.071 --> 00:10.147
the worst criminal offenders are pursued
by the detectives of the Major Case Squad.

00:10.147 --> 00:11.985
These are their stories.

00:13.693 --> 00:15.763
I don't understand why you didn't follow up.

00:15.763 --> 00:18.409
The bleeding is symptomatic 
of everything you checked for.

00:18.409 --> 00:20.035
Eh, it's minor.

00:20.481 --> 00:22.964
And she's 13 years old.
It happens.

00:22.964 --> 00:26.821
If it's all the same to you,
I'm having her rechecked for C.E.M.

00:26.821 --> 00:28.281
Knock yourself out.

00:28.281 --> 00:31.270
I've only been doing this for 20 years.

00:33.538 --> 00:36.074
There's no way anybody knows.

00:36.074 --> 00:38.608
I'm just getting worked up over nothin'.

00:38.608 --> 00:40.644
You usually do.

00:40.793 --> 00:45.149
Hey, Paige, I'd like to think 
I'm not just doing this for me.

00:45.149 --> 00:47.456
It wasn't my idea.

00:50.190 --> 00:52.300
I spoke with him.
Everything is fine.

00:52.300 --> 00:53.997
Don't worry about it.

00:54.628 --> 00:58.408
Mom, we're gonna be late.
Can we motor, please?

01:04.723 --> 01:07.565
Molly said McClintock had
to use the whip this morning.

01:07.565 --> 01:10.152
That's happy news.

01:11.091 --> 01:14.573
Does Paige know how pretty Molly is?

01:16.386 --> 01:20.085
I wouldn't be surprised if he shows up with 
endorsements for teeth whiteners on his saddle.

01:20.085 --> 01:22.765
Lighten up, Megs.
He's putting some zing into the sport.

01:22.765 --> 01:27.116
Oh, really?  I could think of other 
sports in more desperate need of zing.

01:27.116 --> 01:29.644
Speak of the devil.
Hello, Neil.

01:29.644 --> 01:31.774
We werejust talking about  
your terrific streak.   /   Yes.

01:31.774 --> 01:34.967
I heard that you had trouble getting 
your horse over thejumps this morning.

01:34.967 --> 01:39.213
They're showoffs, Mrs. Townsend.
They'll be fine once there's a crowd.

01:39.963 --> 01:44.220
Excuse me.  /  Is that how you're planning 
on winning tomorrow? By getting us all sick?

01:44.824 --> 01:46.963
I have to take this.

01:47.432 --> 01:49.363
Good luck to us all tomorrow.

01:49.998 --> 01:51.479
Yeah.

01:52.360 --> 01:53.897
How bad?

01:54.673 --> 01:56.676
Give me 10 minutes.
I'll meet you out there.

01:56.676 --> 01:59.600
I'm sure we've met before.
Last summer in the Hamptons.

01:59.600 --> 02:01.539
I've never been to the Hamptons.

02:01.539 --> 02:03.085
No? Where do you summer?

02:03.085 --> 02:05.858
Same place I winter.
In Bedford.

02:05.858 --> 02:07.743
Ralph Lauren's Fourth ofJuly barbecue.

02:07.743 --> 02:09.009
You were playing tennis, right?

02:09.009 --> 02:11.537
That's, uh, how you keep this arm so well-toned.

02:11.537 --> 02:16.698
I keep it well-toned by sticking 
it up a cow's rectum once a day.

02:16.753 --> 02:19.524
I'm a vet, and I have patients to see tonight.

02:19.524 --> 02:24.906
My fault. I didn't realize the 
help was invited to this dinner.

02:30.223 --> 02:33.075
What happened? Oh, my God.!
What happened?

02:33.075 --> 02:35.179
What happened?

